latestIgtvVideos.title: Appreciating Margam
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So glad and excited to be a part of this project by my Guru Sri Praveen Kumar ✨

Reposted from @aalaap_concepts • For starters, we love this brand new idea initiated by Shaale in collaboration with Chithkala School of Dance, helmed by acclaimed Bharatanatyam dancer-choreographer-teacher, Praveen Kumar from Bengaluru. 

We are so happy to join hands with them to introduce you - and in detail as we go along - to the premise, intent and outcomes of Understanding & Appreciating a Margam in Bharatanatyam, a brand new online module that is meant for anyone and everyone looking to get familiar and deep dive into the many nuances that go into the process and performance of a traditional Bharatanatyam Margam repertoire. #margam #understanding #appreciation #module #elearning #rasika #nuances #dancer #collaboration @shaaledotcom @praveenkumardance @akhila_krishnamurthy @shreema_upadhyaya @divthedancer @siri_chandrashekar @navya_shree_k_n @hemalatha_sr

latestIgtvVideos.title: Revival of Marga Tala through Alaripu
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A small snippet from the Alaripu choreographed by my Guru Sri P Praveen Kumar in 'Chatchatputa Tala' of 33 aksharas, composed by Sri Guru Bharadwaj, as part of a unique project by GVRNK Foundation. I am so grateful that I could be a part of this, and it has been a wonderful learning experience for me, as I'm sure it will be for all of you. Do register for this e-learning project to learn five different alaripus, set in five Marga Talas.

@praveenkumardance

latestIgtvVideos.title: Trikaala jathi
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
a jathi that always makes my heart happy and knees sore. 

Learning this varna two years ago from @praveenkumardance sir was a milestone of sorts, and also such a turning point, and I am so grateful I got to perform it at a show surrounded by those who have always supported me. This year has well, made me realise what a privilege that is, and how blessed I've been. 

This is a beautiful choreography by my Guru, Sri Praveen Kumar. Kindly do not use this audio or choreography without permission.
